# ls-foundry — core context

Monorepo: **pnpm** workspaces + **Turborepo**. Repo: [github.com/jeffgo10/ls-foundry](https://github.com/jeffgo10/ls-foundry).

## Layout

```
apps/docs/          # Next.js showcase (@ls-foundry/docs) — /stickpak test page
docs/stickpak/      # StickPak Phase 1 docs (mirror Obsidian StickPak/)
packages/           # publishable + internal packages
```

## Package scopes

| Scope | Use | Examples |
|-------|-----|----------|
| `@jeffgo10/*` | **Published** to GitHub Packages (`npm.pkg.github.com`) | `shared-types`, `react-canvas-designer`, `canvas-upscaler`, `helpers`, `gl-viewer` (v0.3.1; consumed by **LiteShadeMedia**) |
| `@ls-foundry/*` | **Private** monorepo-only | `docs`, `tsconfig`, `ui`, `utils`, `maps` |

Publish scope must match GitHub owner (`@jeffgo10`). Bump versions in `packages/*/package.json` before `pnpm run deploy`.

## StickPak Phase 1 packages (current pins)

| Package | Version |
|---------|---------|
| `@jeffgo10/shared-types` | 0.1.2 |
| `@jeffgo10/react-canvas-designer` | 0.1.3 |
| `@jeffgo10/canvas-upscaler` | 0.1.1 |

Always bump `shared-types` first when changing layout/DPI APIs; keep dependent package pins in sync.

## Coding conventions

- **Minimal diffs** — match surrounding style; no drive-by refactors.
- **TypeScript** throughout; build with `tsup` in packages.
- **Canvas transform order:** translate → rotate → scale (top-left origin). Upscaler must match Konva `Group`.
- **Layout JSON** lives in `@jeffgo10/shared-types` — extend types/helpers there before designer or upscaler.
- **Next.js + Konva:** dynamic import `CanvasDesigner`; `transpilePackages: ['@jeffgo10/*']`; `serverExternalPackages: ['canvas']` in `apps/docs/next.config.ts`.
- **Tests:** only when requested or they cover real behavior.
- **Commits/PRs:** only when the user explicitly asks.

## Dev commands

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm run build              # turbo build all
pnpm run build:packages     # packages only
pnpm run dev --filter=@ls-foundry/docs   # → localhost:3000/stickpak
```

## Repo docs (source of truth for agents)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/stickpak/phase-1.md` | Phase 1 checklist, versions, API |
| `docs/stickpak/engineering-notes.md` | Issues/fixes log |
| `docs/stickpak/canvas-scaling.md` | 72→300 DPI math |
| `docs/stickpak/roadmap.md` | Six-phase plan |

When the user asks to update notes, sync **both** repo docs and Obsidian (see `ls-foundry-obsidian-sync.mdc`). Run **`/sync-obsidian-notes`**. Run **`/create-github-pr`** to open a PR (auto branch + commit when on `master`).
